The paper describes the design and implementation of a graduate-level software engineering course, which suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The course also involves hands-on work, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the importance of soft skills, which could relate to cs.ED (Computer Science Education). Finally, the paper discusses the use of technology-agnostic approaches, which could relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
